For release 1, the software for the SATNet server will only be provided for the Debian stable relaase "Wheezy".
This software should also work on Ubuntu and the Debian testing release with minor changes.
Please report any changes on the installation script to the developers through the GitHub website.

Steps to install the server for the SATNet network:

	1) [optional] Install: sudo apt-get install openssh-server sudo git git-core
	2) [optional] Configure user at sudoers: /etc/sudoers
	3) Clone "satnet" repositories into $HOME folder
		git clone https://github.com/satnet-project/server
	4) Execute "setup.sh" script for server installation (within scripts directory).
